Ecosave Holdings pays $4.5m for U.S. building management systems company




        Share  



 Facebook





 Twitter
            


 Google+


 LinkedIn


 Email


 Print


 Download PDF version







13:00 01 Jul 2013









 






Ecosave Holdings (ASX: ECV), which is an energy and water efficiency company, has entered into a sale and purchase agreement to acquire 100% of U.S. based DVL Automation Inc.
Ecosave has completed hundreds of energy and resource savings projects, with the company listing on the ASX earlier in the year with an IPO entry price of $1. Ecosave last traded at $1.61 a handy gain of 61%.Consideration for the deal is $4.5 million, which will be funded through existing cash reserves, scrip and vendor finance.DVL Automation is a provider of building management systems and associated energy efficiency solutions, with the acquisition to deliver Ecosave proprietary Building Management Systems analytics technology to be used in the Australian market.Ecosave has indicated the potential financial impact of the acquisition, which the company said it expects to be able to save a 5-10% of customer’s energy costs.The deal also delivers an installed base of customers in the U.S., into which Ecosave intends to cross-sell its suite of energy efficiency services and Energy Performance Contract services.In regards to the financials of DVL Automation, for the year ending December 2012, the company generated revenues of A$10.1 million and a normalised net profit after tax of A$513,000. The acquisition is earnings accretive for Ecosave.Substantial shareholderPie Funds Management Limited recently became a substantial shareholder of Ecosave, and held a 5.34% stake before today's acquisition was announced.
 
Proactive Investors Australia is the market leader in producing news, articles and research reports on ASX “Small and Mid-cap” stocks with distribution in Australia, UK, North America and Hong Kong / China. 






 





